'''Metro Call-A-Ride''' is the [[paratransit]] service that is provided for people who are elderly and/or dissabled in [[St. Louis]], [[St. Louis County, Missouri|St. Louis County]], and [[St. Clair County, Illinois]]. ==Description== This service consists of a fleet of 136 paratransit vans that do not travel on planned routes like [[MetroBus (St. Louis)|MetroBus]] and [[MetroLink (St. Louis)|MetroLink]]. It provides over 55,000 trips each month to customers with disabilities in Missouri. Call-A-Ride provides service within 1/4 mile from a bus stop. The paratransit service was introduced in 1985. They are kept in the [[Metro Main Shop]].
